Is 2-on-1 Coaching right for you?

This is not a DIY program. You’ll be in constant contact with your team to make sure you get all the guidance and support you need.
Here’s how to know if 2-on-1 coaching is right for you:
You’re busy and struggle to find the time to work out and plan/prep meals consistently - we work around your schedule and lifestyle!
You’ve tried other programs or worked with a trainer before but you didn’t get the results you wanted - if you follow the program you WILL see results.
Some programs have worked initially, but you weren’t able to maintain the results - we equip you with the knowledge you need to maintain now and into the future.
You want to understand the fundamentals of nutrition and exercise better - so you can progress with confidence!
You want to look forward to your workouts instead of them feeling like a chore - you don’t need to struggle with low willpower anymore!

Your team will be with you every step of the way

The BWS coaches and dietitians are experts in the latest, evidence-led approaches to training and nutrition. They help you stay on track and focus on what will get you results. So you never get distracted by the latest fitness trends, scams or fads.

Your coach

Your BWS coach will design a program unique to you and your goals - and will consider:

Your health, any injuries and experiences
The equipment you have access to - you don’t need anything fancy or elaborate!
Your schedule and lifestyle - most of our clients are busy professionals with limited time available

You’ll also be in regular contact by email, text and calls.

Your dietitian

Your BWS dietitian will design a unique eating plan that will help you achieve your goals, and will consider:

Your health and background
Dietary restrictions and food preferences - you won’t have to give up your favorites!
Your schedule and lifestyle

You’ll also be in regular contact by email, text and calls.

You!

You won’t get contradicting advice or guesswork when you work with BWS. Everything is designed for you, so you can finally feel in control and focused.

And you’ll love how much momentum and motivation you get when you’re not wasting energy on filtering what information to trust.

GOT QUESTIONS?

That’s normal. Actually, that’s GREAT – it shows you truly care about your results.
If you’re wondering about anything, I’ve answered a list of the most commonly asked questions below:

Do I need access to a gym or can I train from home?
It doesn’t matter whether you’re training at home or you have access to a gym. Our expert coaches will be able to tailor everything PERSONALIZED to you and the equipment you have available.
I’ve tried other programs in the past, what makes this different?
You’re going to be able to achieve your physique goals while working with your dietitian to still incorporate your favorite foods into your lifestyle. You’re also going to have expert coaches and a dietitian not just guide you to your goals, but also to educate you throughout the journey so that you can maintain the results long term. 

Your coach and dietitian will help hold you accountable to achieving your goals.
How soon can I start the Built With Science 2 on 1 Coaching Program?
Take action today! Book your discovery call to enroll into our program and begin your onboarding. A questionnaire will be sent to you upon signing up so that our coaches and dietitians can assess your goals in more detail.


Once this has been completed and returned to your coach, your PERSONALIZED plan will be complete for you within one week.


The questionnaire will also help to determine which of our coaches would best fit your goals.
I am a beginner: will this still work for me?
Yes, absolutely. In short, the Built With Science 2-on-1 Coaching Program is for all ability levels.

 Regardless of whether you’re a beginner trainee, or if you’re a more advanced trainee, our expert coaches and dietitians will be able to customize your nutrition and training to suit your ability level and also your goals.
I HAVE AN INJURY, CAN I STILL SIGN UP TO THE BUILT WITH SCIENCE 2-ON-1 COACHING PROGRAM?
Yes. We would have to diagnose this in more detail on the consultation call. However, we can work around most injuries and make the training program PERSONALIZED to your goals, while working around any injuries you have.
I have a food intolerance; will this still work for me?
This is not an issue at all. Our dietitians will work with you to learn how to incorporate the food that you are able to tolerate into your diet while also meeting your nutrition needs. 
Do I have to track every single macro and meal prep?
Our dietitians want to work with you to develop a nutrition strategy that is sustainable and enjoyable for you. We don’t want you to track for the rest of your life, and we’ll teach you how to do this!
You don’t need to meal prep every single meal if that’s not something that you enjoy. You and your dietitian will develop a strategy together that works best for you, your lifestyle, your schedule, and your preference while still meeting your goals.
How many hours per week do I need to commit to training?
Our expert coaches can customize the session length to whatever time you can commit to training. However, for best results, you will ideally need to be able to complete at least 3-4 sessions per week for 30 minutes.
How soon will I start seeing results?
This is not a quick fix program! Extreme diets or training modalities may get you quick results, but are far from sustainable. Our expert team of coaches and dietitians will provide you with the structure and support you need to have long-term and sustainable results. What we need from you is consistency, dedication, and willingness to trust the process!
After the phone consultation if I don’t think the program is a good fit for me, do I still have to sign up?
This isn't an issue at all. In short, the discovery call is intended to give you all the information you need to feel confident about the services and support we offer during the program.  Reminder: This is a discovery call with an enrollment representative on our team and will not be a consultation call with a personal trainer or registered dietitian. The 2-on-1 Coaching program is a separate paid service from our main programs if you decide to move forward.
Can I get a refund?
Yes, find out more about our refund policy on a call with our enrolment members!
What kind of client do you work with?
All of the coaches and dietitians on our team value every single client that they get to work with and transform their lives for the better. The clients that they have worked with and have consistently seen achieve the best results are clients who are open to learning, develop consistency, and trust the process and their expertise.
